text.section:
"Waters of the State" includes:
Both surface and underground waters within the boundaries of the State subject to its jurisdiction;
That portion of the Atlantic Ocean within the boundaries of the State;
The Chesapeake Bay and its tributaries;
All ponds, lakes, rivers, streams, public ditches, tax ditches, and public drainage systems within the State, other than those designed and used to collect, convey, or dispose of sanitary sewage; and
The floodplain of free-flowing waters determined by the Department of the Environment on the basis of the 100-year flood frequency.
